'''Richard Clayderman''' ({{bd|1953-ngièn|12-ngie̍t 28-ngit||}}) he [[Fap-koet]] ke yit-chak [[kông-khìm]]-kâ.

Clayderman ngièn-lòi ke miàng-sṳ ham-cho '''Philippe Pagès''', chhai Fap-koet [[Pâ-lì]] chhut-se, 6 se khôi-sṳ́ ho̍k [[kông-khìm]], 12 se sṳ̀-heu pûn [[Pâ-lì Yîm-ngo̍k Ho̍k-yen]] (''Conservatoire de Paris'') liu̍k-chhí. [[1976-ngièn]], yîm-ngo̍k chṳ-phién-ngìn [[Olivier Toussaint]] lâu [[Paul de Senneville]] chhiáng kì cho yîm-ngo̍k chôn-si̍p liu̍k-yîm,<ref>[http://www.clayderman.co.uk/olivier_toussaint_interview.htm Clayderman.co.uk]</ref> kì thàn kông-khìm-khiuk ''[[Ballade pour Adeline]]'' (''Pûn Adeline ke Ballad''), liá-chak chôn-si̍p chhai 38 chak koet-kâ mai chhut 2200 van chông.<ref>[http://www.clayderman.co.uk/biography.htm "Biography, Richard Clayderman"]</ref>

Richard Clayderman he sṳ-kie chhut-miàng ke kông-khìm-kâ, yû 1,300 khiuk kông-khìm-khiuk. Kì chhai [[2010-ngièn]] lâu Typhaine kiet-fûn, hien-chhai sâng-fa̍t chhai Fap-koet [[Île-de-France]] ke [[Saint-Ouen (Seine-Saint-Denis)|Saint-Ouen]].

